roomeq (0.6.1) bookworm; urgency=medium

  * Added high-performance Rust-based optimizer (roomeq-optimizer binary)
  * Rust optimizer provides 10-20x faster processing than Python implementation
  * Full algorithm compatibility with Python version maintained
  * JSON stdin/stdout interface for seamless integration
  * Real-time progress reporting via stdout
  * Support for all biquad filter types (HP/LP/EQ/Shelf/Notch)
  * Complete documentation and examples included
  * Man page for roomeq-optimizer command

 -- HiFiBerry <support@hifiberry.com>  Mon, 19 Aug 2025 12:00:00 +0000

roomeq (0.6.0) bookworm; urgency=medium

  * Advanced EQ optimization system with SciPy integration
  * Comprehensive biquad filter implementation (HP/LP/BP/Notch/Peaking/Shelving)
  * Real-time optimization progress reporting with configurable intervals
  * Expert classification system for target curves and optimizer presets
  * API key serving for both target curves and optimizer presets
  * Enhanced REST API with intermediate results support
  * Target curve management with expert/beginner categorization
  * Optimizer preset system with multiple algorithms and parameters
  * Custom JSON serialization for complex optimization results
  * Comprehensive API documentation with curl examples
  * Version endpoint with detailed feature list and server information
  * Complete migration from old RoomEQ system to new REST API architecture

 -- HiFiBerry <support@hifiberry.com>  Sun, 18 Aug 2025 12:00:00 +0000

roomeq (0.3.0) bookworm; urgency=medium

  * Major API enhancements and new features
  * Migrated from FastAPI/uvicorn to Flask framework
  * Added comprehensive FFT spectral analysis functionality
  * Implemented modular FFT module (fft.py) for code organization
  * Added FFT normalization feature for relative dB measurements
  * Enhanced sine sweep generation with multiple consecutive sweeps
  * Implemented background audio recording system with secure file management
  * Added comprehensive recording management endpoints (start/stop/download/delete)
  * Fixed alsaaudio compatibility issues with PY_SSIZE_T_CLEAN macro
  * Updated comprehensive API documentation with new endpoints
  * Added windowing functions support (Hann, Hamming, Blackman)
  * Implemented frequency band analysis (sub-bass through brilliance)
  * Added peak detection and spectral centroid calculation
  * Enhanced error handling and parameter validation
  * Added CORS support for web application integration
  * Improved logging and debugging capabilities

 -- HiFiBerry <support@hifiberry.com>  Thu, 15 Aug 2025 12:00:00 +0000

